      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SECRET SERVICE AGENT NZ (3) has tackled handy races in both starts since a spell, coming from a wide draw for a resuming second before he finished fourth in the Graduation Series 3YO final at Maryborough. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position and should be close to his peak now. This is a nice drop in class so he can deliver. Hard to knock TALKBABYTALK (2) who made it a hat trick of wins when he led and scored by 2.5 metres at Geelong last week. Up in grade but is proven at this circuit and distance and a low draw could see him add to the winning streak. TALISKER SKIPPER (1) is another in fine form, scoring back-to-back wins before a second at Kilmore last week. All of those were from tougher barriers so he is well served by the ace draw. IM DUSTEE (4) could be close to a win after placing in the last three outings, last week coming from the back row to miss by a nose at Shepparton.",
